p to broaden his readership in Germany and abroad.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aLawxPhilosophy. 4aPrivatrecht. 7aLAW / Civil Law.2bisacsh  aPrivate Law.1 aGrigoleit, Hans Christoph, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNeuner, Jörg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Law - 2000 - 2014z9783110636208oZDB-23-GLA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET RECHTSWISSENSCHAFTEN 2012z9783110288919oZDB-23-DGC0 cprintz978311027392240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311027403540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110274035423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110274035/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGCb2012  aZDB-23-DGGb2012  aZDB-23-GLAc2000d2014